import numpy as np

# Index trick when working with two np-arrays
a = np.array([1, 2, 3, 6, 1, 4, 1])

# Saves every spot in a except at index where b != 1

x = np.array([4, 6, 8, 1, 2, 6, 9])
y = x > 5
print(x[y])
# >>> [6 8 6 9]

# Even shorter

# >>> [1 2 3 4 4]
